name: integer_i8_negative_one
description: |
  This is -1, represented with every bit set in two's-complement i8. It is the
  divisor that makes i8 minimum division overflow, and it commonly exposes
  differences between arithmetic and logical right shifts, sign extension,
  and signed-to-unsigned conversion. The same byte represents u8 maximum.
format: hex
decode-as: i8
pair:
  - with: ../u8/maximum.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i8"
  - "negative"
  - "division"
  - "sign-extension"
  - "conversion"
  - "two's-complement"
  - "all-bits-set"
---
ff   # -1
